-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Thu Mar 13, 2014 05:59AM EDT
-- None



March 13 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Thursday:

** French conglomerate Bouygues <BOUY.PA> enriched the cash element of its offer for media group Vivendi's <VIV.PA> telecoms unit SFR in an attempt to seal a deal and shut out rival bidder Numericable <NUME.PA>. Bouygues said it would increase the cash portion of the bid to 11.3 billion euros ($15.7 billion) from 10.5 billion previously, while reducing the stake Vivendi is left with in the combined SFR-Bouygues telecoms business to 43 percent, from 46 percent previously. [ID:nL6N0MA11N]  ** New Zealand is seeking to raise as much as NZ$800 million ($680 million) through the sale of a minority stake in power company Genesis Energy Ltd [GEPWR.UL], setting a low price range and offering other sweeteners to draw investors to the last of its state asset sales. [ID:nL3N0MA1AM]  ** Vocus Inc <VOCS.O>, a provider of cloud marketing software, is looking to sell itself and has attracted interest from industry rivals and private equity firms, according to several people familiar with the matter. [ID:nL2N0M926U]  ** Spanish builder ACS <ACS.MC>, which has been cutting its stake in Iberdrola <IBE.MC>, said it planned to issue a five-year bond of around 400 million euros that could be exchanged into shares of the power company. [ID:nL6N0MA0TO]